<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Situational.  They're all situational.<P>   Air: when you want stun, usually versus casters.  Fast speed, plus invis, makes this the only pet at all safe to run around with.  Can be a surprise factor if you're PvP.  Good cold resistance.<P>   Fire: when you face fast-hitting mobs, especially monk types.  Really begins to shine at higher levels, simply because the innate fire shield is better than the mage one, that the other pets will have.  Low hitpoints reduce effectiveness for tanking.  Nice damage output with the DD.  Good fire resistance.<P>   Earth: gobs o' hitpoints if you need a damage sponge, root if you're desperate to hold a mob (any PC spell in the group will be a better choice).  Good disease resistance (?).<P>   Water: nice damage output with the DD as well as melee.  Good regen.  Good poison resistance.<P>   I'd base my choice on the characteristics of the pets, rather than simply my level.  They all have a use.  Everyone has their favorites, of course.   TBut there's no "one best pet" for all situations.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
