<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I'd like to add a couple of side notes.<P>1) Make sure you out damage your pet in a fight.  If your pet does more damage to a mob than you, you'll get a lot less experience.  I heard that a Fire pet's damage shield doesn't count as the pet's damage.<P>2) If you fight casters, memorize either Cancel Magic or Nullify Magic (depending on your level).  Use them to pull casters.  Casters tend to buff themselves.  Getting rid of their buff can have a visible effect on the pet's fight against certain types of mobs.  For example, if the mob has SoW, the pet will be chasing the mob for a while, or if the mob has a damage shield, your pet will take a lot more damage.  This is kind of a judgement call, there won't be a visible effect with ALL casters, just certain types.<P>3) Earth Elementals are terrible in groups.<P>Drew Davis has done an excellent job describing the pets so I won't repeat the work.<P>--------------------<P>Jimm The Magician<BR>Magician of the 40th Season<BR>Luclin
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
