You'll use an earth pet alot at higher levels if you're going to be chain casting.  When chain casting you want your pet to last alot longer,   but also get hit more so the DS does more damage.  The earth pet does this...it has the HP to get hit more and the low agility to get hit more often.  The root also helps during pet recast by often letting you get the new pet buffed before the root breaks.<BR>Like they were saying...its situational.  And earth pets don't always suck for groups.  In a group with no snarer, the mage earth pet can be the difference between consistant quick pulling and a train caused by a runner.<P>--------------------<P>Tomlyn Drayke-Lvl 53 Elementalist<BR>Falkan Strydewell-Lvl 39 Paladin<BR>Fallken-Lvl 16 Rogue<BR>Sigmacrunk-Lvl 11 Iksar Shaman<BR>Prexus<P>"But whosoever should cross that line, into true corruption,into our domain....One day you will look behind you and you will see We Three, and on that day, YOU WILL REAP IT!" ---"Boondock Saints"
