<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
erm...if you're going to solo, i would recommend a earth pet.  <P>normally, pull with malise/malisement/etc (cancel/nullify for casters, but follow with malise/malisement/malosi right after that) and then send your pet in to attack it.  hold off doing great damage until the mob is solidly agroed on your pet.  remember to cast DS on your earth pet before you do all this so you can inflict more damage on the mob.  start off with a rain spell and then start nuking to finish off the mob.  (your pet won't last too long later on against stronger mobs lvl 38-45 mobs)  when you reach lvl 44, you'll enjoy the dot spell you get.  that will help with you doing damage faster while limiting the amount of hate you build on the mobs hate list.  remember, rain as a dot and then elemental maelstrom/wrath of elements for later lvls.  this is all to work the hate list.  <P>group...fire or water pets work well if you have a tank or 2 in the group.  <P>note: though some people say earth pets aren't good to have in a group due to varies reasons, i found that this is not true.  many times, especially in zones like OT, an add can be kept busy by your earth pet while the rest of the group can finish off the first pull.  many times our group had to fight 3 mobs at once, my earth pet proved to be more than just great.  learn to retarget stuff while in groups and you should be okay.  good luck.
</FONT>
