<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I just want to start this out by saying this is not a bash of the earth pet.  Earth is probably the safest pet to solo with.  The protection of a root cannot be overstated.  But earth is not the only pet for soloing, and there's not suddenly a level where you have to use it like you'll commonly hear.<P>I personally prefer water.  Much higher AC, better regen, and does more damage.  I always use signficantly less mana when I kill something with a water pet compared to an earth, and still get the 51%+ damage for the xp.  Now to use the water (or other) pet you have to know how not to overburn.  You've got to have patience and let your pet suck up some damage at first when your instinct is to nuke and nuke again.  If you aggro the mob don't panic, just run through your pet until it aggros on him again, and don't immediately nuke it again once it does - more patience required.<P>I've had a lot of success using other pets for soloing.  The fire pet also can work well and some people swear by it, but damn things can go wrong fast.  Air works extremely well, tho I just personally prefer damage-dealers.<P>One last recommendation.  If you're going to be using a pet other than earth for soloing, I would strongly recommend a combination of AC and HP gear, since you won't be able to burn all of your mana anyways.<P>So the point of this message is use whichever pet you're comfortable with for soloing.  There's not necessarily one that's generally better.  For every pet you'll find a mage who makes the case that it's the best for soloing. My personal opinion is that to be a good mage you need to learn to adapt the pet you're using to the situation you're in.<P>--------------------<P>Vdir Zryyxln<BR>Soldier of the Teir`Dal Templar<BR>Rallos Zek
</FONT>
