<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Some swear by Fire, some swear by Earth, some swear by Water, and some swear by Air.  Don't assume one pet is better than any of the others.  If someone swears by one type, read way he does, they'll generally have good reasons for liking that pet.<P>What I'm doing in fights with my Fire Elemental is this.  I'll tell it to attack and the moment it's engaged in a battle, I'll use the level 24 spell Shock of Spikes.  It seems to have less taunt than Blaze or Cinder Bolt.  I cast Shock of Spikes twice, wait for the mob to be just under have life then I blast it with Blaze or Cinder Bolt.  The mob generally runs at this point and I don't take a single point of damage.  I fight like this with mobs that I know either won't kill the Fire Elemental or will kill it on it's last leg, just before it runs.  This is what works for me, each person has their own style and is use to using specific pet for that style.  You just need to figure out what your style is and pick the pet(s) that best fit it.<P>BTW, you'll love the regeneration that the level 39 pets have.  It's nice to have a pet at 30 percent health only to have it at full health in less than a minute.<P>--------------------<P>Jimm The Magician<BR>Magician of the 40th Season<BR>Luclin
