oh ya one more thing... there are different tactics to use with each pet, for different enemies...<BR>obviously each pet is better suited vr. different creatures... but also using a single pet you can change your tactics to fit different creatures as well...<P>IE you have a sow, and can get one easily whle you fight...  get one for your pet... engage pet... nuke hard till it agros you... then run around with the pet beating it up from behind till it agroes the pet, then blast again... this way the pet lasts a lot longer and takes significantly less damage<P>also chain casting at higher levels can help when your camping a tough mob or something and with normal tactics you would't be able to kill it...<P>try to save up and buy every pet you can at each level (lower levels you can get by with only buying 1 or 2 if you dont have the cash but its betteR) then everytime you go to a new hunting grounds with new monsters, try each pet for a whiel.. see which one you are safer/kill faster/more efficient/kill harder mobs, etc.
