<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
In the light of all these different opinions, I guess I can only speak for myself.<P>At lower levels I loved my water pet. I used it almost exclusively when soloing and in groups. It has almost the hp of an earth pet and just seems to do a lot more damage hitting and nuking. I was also able to kill all the snakes no one ever bothered with because the water does not have a problem with the poison. At lower levels I really did not need root a lot. Just practiced not overburning so mob would rarely come after me. Well somewhere along the line the mobs get tougher. No longer does blue mean I can take this thing. It means a group can take this thing and I can take low blues. You have to change with that.<P>From my experience if you solo, don't use anything except earth. Period. End of conversation. Sure you can play around with using the other pets, but just not worth it to me. The higher you go the tougher the mobs are. For example at lvl 51 - 54 I soloed a lot in Burning Woods. You take on a lvl 45 war boned skeleton or a lvl 45 gorilla and see how long your pet lasts. Heh. I could just kill one of them before my pet died. That is the highest level earth pet hitting for 58. Other pets do not have the hp to take on these mobs. In the 40's I soloed some in the Emerald jungle. Most pets can handle low blues, but never know when you are going to pull a high blue. Too late your pet is dead and you probably are too (I never did get jboots). In short, above about lvl 25...just use earth to solo.<P>In group up to lvl 50, use whatever works best in each situation. Each pet has uses for each kind of mob and dungeon. Just experiment. After level 51 though you will find yourself using the 51 earth pet the most until you get the 53 air pet. That is my favorite in dungeons because the stun comes in so handy. I just now got 54 water so will start experimenting with it. I will probably be switching back and forth between air and water now unless tankage is needed.<P>Final summary - play with whatever pet you have the most fun with. In soloing I bet you will use earth though because you will have more fun running/dying less.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Bemidian<BR>56 Erudite Conjurer
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
 Posts: <B>88</B>  &nbsp;|&nbsp; IP: <A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_ip&f=6&t=004134&reply_num=000013">Logged</A>
</FONT>
</td></tr>
</table>
</td></tr>


